---
title:  Loaded Potato, Broccoli & Bacon Skillet 3 easy steps to a delicious dinner
description: Got one pan and 15 minutes to spare? That’s all you need to get this filling, flavorful skillet meal on the table. First you’ll crisp up smoky bacon, then use those magic drippings to sauté broccoli, grape tomatoes, and potatoes to perfection. Sprinkle it all with melty cheddar, then serve with sour cream, ranch dressing, and hot sauce for diners to drizzle as desired.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/677d632ba90519950138cdef-f1f0610e.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/677d632ba90519950138cdef-en-US.pdf
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 47 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 32 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 21 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1230 mg
author: HelloFresh
time required: 15 minutes
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/loaded-potato-broccoli-and-bacon-skillet-677d632ba90519950138cdef
cuisine: North America
---

Wash and dry produce.

Cut @bacon{4%ounce} crosswise into 1/2-inch pieces.

Heat a large dry, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add bacon
and cook, stirring occasionally, until bacon begins to crisp and fat renders,
~{4%minutes}. (The bacon will finish cooking in the next step.)

Meanwhile, in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @broccoli{8%ounce},
@garlic powder{1%tsp}, 1 TBSP water (2 TBSP for 4 servings), a pinch of
@salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until
tender, ~{1-2%minutes}. Set aside for use in the next step.

Add @seasoned precooked potato slices{10%ounce} and @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}
to pan with bacon; season with a pinch of salt and pepper. (If there's not
enough bacon fat, add a drizzle of @?oil{}.) Cook, undisturbed, until potatoes
are crispy on one side and bacon is cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes}. Stir,
gently scraping up any crispy bits on the bottom.

> TIP: If potatoes start to stick to the pan, add a splash of water.

Top potato skillet with broccoli. Sprinkle everything with @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}.
Cover and cook until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide potato, broccoli, and bacon skillet between plates. Serve with
@sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, @buttermilk ranch dressing{1.5%ounce}, and
@hot sauce{1%tsp} on the side.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.